---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { t, localizedPath } from "../i18n/utils";

const lang = "en" as const;
---

<BaseLayout title={t(lang, "about.title")} description={t(lang, "about.subtitle")} lang={lang}>
  <div class="fade-in">
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-extrabold text-ink sm:text-4xl">{t(lang, "about.title")}</h1>
    <p class="mb-10 mt-3 text-lg text-neutral-400">{t(lang, "about.subtitle")}</p>
  </div>

  <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none fade-in">
    <p>
      Jorsby is a <strong>vertical AI drama studio</strong>. We produce binge-worthy,
      short-form drama series — the kind people actually finish — for brands that want
      attention they can't buy with another banner ad.
    </p>

    <p>
      Drama is the oldest growth hack there is. People will sit through fifteen episodes
      of a story they care about and skip a fifteen-second ad without a thought. So we
      don't make ads. We make <strong>series</strong>: characters, tension, cliffhangers,
      a reason to come back tomorrow — built for the vertical feed where your audience
      already lives.
    </p>

    <h2>How we work</h2>

    <p>
      We write, produce, voice and edit entire episodic series with AI. That collapses
      what used to take a crew, a cast and a calendar into a pipeline that turns a brief
      into launch-ready episodes in days — and lets us ship the same story in every
      language you sell in, with localized voices instead of subtitles.
    </p>

    <h2>The launch series</h2>

    <p>
      <em>The Glass Tower</em> is our first series — a fifteen-episode corporate thriller,
      produced end to end to show what the format can do. Watch it on the{" "}
      <a href={localizedPath("/work", lang)}>work page</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Who's behind it</h2>

    <p>
      <strong>Serhat</strong> — founder. Builds the production pipeline, directs the
      stories and obsesses over the first three seconds of every episode.
    </p>

    <h2>Work with us</h2>

    <p>
      If you want a series that sells for your brand, <a href={localizedPath("/contact", lang)}
        >tell us what you're launching</a
      > — we'll come back with a concept and a quote before you commit to anything.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
